Cluster Analysis

Ward hierarchical clustering with bootstrapped p values.

# Prep data
IrrClst<-na.omit(as.matrix(DemoAna[c('WLS1','RPQRACen','RPQPACen',
                                     'DASSAnxCen','DASSDepCen',
                                     'AQPACen','AQVACen','AQACen','AQHCen')]))
IrrClst<-scale(IrrClst)
colnames(IrrClst)<-c('Irritability','RPQ Reactive Agg.','RPQ Proactive Agg.',
                  'DASS Anxiety','DASS Depression','AQ Physical Agg.',
                  'AQ Verbal Agg.', 'AQ Anger', 'AQ Hostility')


# Ward Hierarchical Clustering with Bootstrapped p values
pvfit <- pvclust(IrrClst, method.hclust="ward.D2",
               method.dist="euclidean")
## Bootstrap (r = 0.5)... Done.
## Bootstrap (r = 0.6)... Done.
## Bootstrap (r = 0.7)... Done.
## Bootstrap (r = 0.8)... Done.
## Bootstrap (r = 0.9)... Done.
## Bootstrap (r = 1.0)... Done.
## Bootstrap (r = 1.1)... Done.
## Bootstrap (r = 1.2)... Done.
## Bootstrap (r = 1.3)... Done.
## Bootstrap (r = 1.4)... Done.
plot(pvfit,float=.03, print.num=F,
     cex.pv=1.2, col.pv=c(1,0,1),
     cex=1.2,cex.axis=1.2,cex.lab=1.2,
     main='',xlab='') # dendogram with p values
# add rectangles around groups highly supported by the data
pvrect(pvfit, alpha=.95, lwd=3)

RMET Analysis

# WLS1 = irritability

fRMET<-lm(RMET_PercentAcc_recoded~WLS1*Gender+VocabCen+AgeCen,
           data=na.omit(DemoAna[DemoAna$RMET_PercentAcc_recoded>25,
                        c("WLS1","Gender","AgeCen",
                        "VocabCen","RMET_PercentAcc_recoded")]))

# Estimate Relative Importance of Predictors
fHABred<-lm(SIPHAB~WLS1+DASSAnxCen+RPQRACen+Gender+VocabCen+AgeCen,
            data=DemoAna)
boot <- boot.relimp(fHABred, b = 1000, 
                    type = c("lmg"), rank = TRUE, 
                    diff = TRUE, rela = TRUE)
booteval.relimp(boot) # print result
